 the temple. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=alindawyl>Alindawyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/1/02 2:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ancient Jar</span><hr size=1> I guess I should say he paths within spitting distance of the bottom of the steps in front of the temple, not the entrance itself at the top of the steps.  From the base of the steps you can easily see him as he walks by, even if your clip plane is at 50% or maybe even less.  Unless it's changed recently.  Last time I killed him was about three months ago. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uellocopato.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ellocopato</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 271<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/16/02 11:22 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ancient Jar</span><hr size=1> does he despawn or will stay up until killed?<br>
